<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Resolved</Status>
<Resolution>The "Operation: Monorepo Genesis" task plan was created to execute a full restructure into a clean monorepo architecture, governed by a "Safe-Delete" protocol to prevent data loss.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_AgentPersona_Flaw">
<Timestamp>2025-08-20T21:12:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>A critical architectural flaw in DevEnviro.as was identified: AgentPersona objects are inefficiently and incorrectly reconstructed from database records instead of using live, in-memory instances, leading to runtime inconsistency.</Summary>
<Priority>CRITICAL</Priority>
<Status>Active</Status>
<Resolution>A critical-priority task (AgentRegistry_Refactor) has been created to refactor the AgentRegistry to be the single source of truth for live agent objects and implement in-memory management with persistence hooks.</Resolution>
</Incident>
<Incident id="incident_Gemini_CLI_Listener_Restart_Loop">
<Timestamp>2025-09-12T23:45:00Z</Timestamp>
<Summary>The DevEnviro Gemini CLI Listener container is stuck in a restart loop, preventing any agent-based interactions with the core orchestrator.</Summary>
<Priority>High</Priority>
<Status>Active</Status>
<Resolution>No resolution has been planned yet. The issue needs to be investigated by analyzing container logs.</Resolution>
</Incident>
</Incidents>
<KnowledgeBase>
<Topic label="Strategic Operations">
<Description>High-level strategic plans governing the evolution of the ApexSigma ecosystem.</Description>
<Node id="Operation_Asgard_Rebirth" label="Operation Asgard Rebirth: Implementation & Correction">
<Detail>
<Summary>An umbrella operation focused on closing the critical implementation gaps identified in the verification report. It encompasses all corrective actions, including the 'Monorepo Genesis' and 'memOS Upgrade' operations.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Operation_Monorepo_Genesis" label="Operation: Monorepo Genesis">
<Detail>
<Summary>A focused operation to resolve the chaotic project directory structure by migrating all code and artifacts into a structured monorepo. It is governed by the TPGP and MAR protocols and includes a "Safe-Delete" workflow to prevent data loss during the transition.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Operation_memOS_Upgrade" label="Operation: memOS Upgrade">
<Detail>
<Summary>A focused, three-phase operation to upgrade the memOS.as service. It is governed by the TPGP and MAR protocols and aims to solidify the core service, integrate an orchestrator, and deploy an intelligence layer.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
</Topic>
<Topic label="Governance & Protocols">
<Description>The immutable laws and protocols that govern the ecosystem's development and operation.</Description>
<Node id="TPGP" label="TaskMaster Generation Protocol (TPGP)">
<Detail>
<Summary>The standard for creating all task plans. It mandates dual-output (Markdown for humans, POML for machines), per-task MAR roles (Implementer, Reviewer), explicit 'Done means Done' criteria, and a sequential workflow handoff protocol where the Reviewer's sign-off is the trigger for continuation.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="MAR_Protocol" label="MAR (Mandatory Agent Review) Protocol">
<Detail>
<Summary>A formal, mandatory quality gatekeeper workflow where a designated Reviewer agent must formally approve an Implementer agent's work on a task before the project can proceed. It is a core component of our multi-agent collaboration framework, designed to catch errors and strategic misalignments early.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Omega_Ingest_Laws" label="Omega Ingest Laws">
<Detail>
<Summary>A set of binding laws governing all interactions with the Omega Ingest master knowledge graph. Key tenets include the principles of a Single Source of Truth (the KG is the definitive record), Immutability of Verified Data (no alteration of verified facts), and a mandatory Dual Verification Requirement for all new entries to ensure accuracy and prevent drift.</Summary>
</Detail>
</Node>
<Node id="Safe_Delete_Protocol" label="Safe-Delete Protocol">
<Detail>
<Summary>A workflow to prevent accidental data loss, primarily during the monorepo restructure. Instead of permanent deletion, the `rm` and `del` commands are overridden by shell functions to move files to a temporary `_archive/trash` directory, from which they can be recovered or permanently deleted later.</Summary>
<CodeSnippet language="bash">
<![CDATA[
# Overrides the 'rm' command to move files to the workspace archive.
rm() {
    local TRASH_DIR="/path/to/your/ApexSigmaProjects.Dev/_archive/trash"
    mkdir -p "$TRASH_DIR"
    if [ "$#" -eq 0 ]; then
        # If no arguments, call the original rm (e.g., for 'rm -i')
        command rm
        return
    fi
    for target in "$@"; do
        mv -v "$target" "$TRASH_DIR"
    done
}
]]>
</CodeSnippet>
</Detail>
</Node>
</Topic>
